<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="G" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Governor" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Governor,</orth> 1) one invested with supreme authority: <cit><quote>her lord, her g., her king,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mv 3.2.167" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. III, 2, 167</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. shr 5.2.138" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. V, 2, 138</bibl>. <cit><quote>Rome's gracious g.</quote> <bibl n="shak. tit 5.3.146" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. V, 3, 146</bibl></cit> (== emperor).<lb />2) one who rules a country or place with delegated authority: <bibl n="shak. mm 1.2.164" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. I, 2, 164</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 1.2.164" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. I, 2, 164</bibl> <bibl n="shak. r2 2.1.220" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 II, 1, 220</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 3.3.1" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 III, 3, 1</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.4.20" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 4, 20</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 4.1.3" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 3</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.1.89" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B IV, 1, 89</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 2.1.30" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. II, 1, 30</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 2.1.30" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. II, 1, 30</bibl> <bibl n="shak. oth 5.2.367" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 367</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 1.4.56" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. I, 4, 56</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 1.4.56" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. I, 4, 56</bibl> <bibl n="shak. per 4.6.57" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 6, 57</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 4.6.57" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 6, 57</bibl> <bibl n="shak. per 5.1.4" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 4</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 5.1.4" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 4</bibl> <bibl n="shak. per 5.1.4" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 4</bibl>
<lb />3) one who has the care of a young man, a tutor: <emph>being ordained his</emph> (the young king's) <cit><quote>special g.</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.1.171" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 1, 171</bibl></cit>.
